<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40032a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40032a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40032a"> 32(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> for the duration</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <i>Chuhras</i> made good soldiers, and served in Mesopotamia, France, and other fields during the war. Many outcastes, indeed, joined the army, the labour corps especially, &ldquo;for the duration,&rdquo; and brought back to their people strange tales of the great world. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI1"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 35</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09250j" href="c9all.htm#c09250j">VI.C.09:250(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
